The paper deals with text simplification, which is a natural language processing task. The use of semantic parsing and neural machine translation suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The evaluation of the proposed method also involves measuring the similarity between the original and simplified texts, which could fall under Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the use of neural methods suggests that the paper could also belong to Neural Networks (cs.NE).
